<br>
Here's what I've noticed (verify please.. I could be wrong).  There is an 8 spawn cycle which for me (at least for the part I started checking on) consisted of:<br>
<br>
1.  grol baku soldier<br>
2.  darkwing bat<br>
3.  grol baku soldier<br>
4.  grol baku soldier<br>
5.  darkwing bat<br>
6.  darkwing bat<br>
7.  TORMENTED Vah Shir Skeleton<br>
8.  darkwing bat<br>
<br>
The only thing that seemed to vary was #7, which was sometimes the skelly and sometimes another spawn which I took to be the skelly's placeholder.  You'd have to kill them all, but at least you'd have an idea of when one might pop.<br>
<br>
I'm a shaman so I set up the cat detector van (my pet Woofie) out ahead of me (maybe 10 feet in real terms) as I sat with my back to the wall.  Unless one of the spawns on the cycle was up, Woofie was facing out watching sonic wolves and other irrelevant stuff.  When there was a pop, I could tell where it was from which direction he was facing.  If he was facing me, the spawn was inside the wall and I could get ready for it.<br>
<br>
If you draw a line from about 2 feet out from the wall and maybe 20 feet along its length (real terms.. you'll know what I mean when you camp it) to the outer edge of the tree, the spawn area is anywhere behind the wall-tree line and in front of zone edge, including inside or over the tree and inside the wall.  The pet helps here, because he'll be essentially facing backwards, away from the other normal zone spawns.<br>
<br>
Btw, the 4th F9 view is very helpful here so you can see the whole area including your dog and yourself.  On one occasion, the cat popped up nearly next to the tree and almost wandered away before I caught him<br>
<br>
It took approximately 12 hours to collect 8 skulls, so the time estimate is fairly accurate.<br>
<br>
Merro Xmas<br>
57 Shaman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubanshiredarkfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banshire Darkfire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 10:06:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3531.topic&index=129>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tormented Vah Shir</span><hr size=1> Anyone know the approx lvl of the skellies that spawn AFTER the courier is killed?<br>
